content:
Weekly Schedule

ICS-33: Intermediate Programming

For an alternative presentation of the listing of course materials, see the Lectures/Lab Schedule page.

Pre-class (No classes this week, but examine these materials)

  • 9/26: Lab
    • Download and Install Python, Java, and Eclipse.
      Work through Python Programming in the Eclipse IDE
    • Start Program #0: Eclipse Python and Debugger Perspective
      (due on Thursday, 10/3, at 11:30pm)

  • 9/27: Lecture
    • Course Overview
      Problems: 1, 3, 5, 9
    • A Review of File Reading
      Problem 1

Week 1

  • Monday (9/30): Lecture
    • Review Python I: start - Parallel/Tuple/List Assignments Problems 1-9
    • Interesting Graphs
    • Picturing Lists / Class Objects / A Function returning a Function
    • Python Binding Worksheet
    • Creating/Using a List of Functions
    • Distribute Academic Integrity Contract
      (please read for discussion at next lecture)

  • Tuesday (10/1): Lab
    • Work on Program #0: Eclipse Python and Debugger Perspective
      (due on Thursday, 10/3, at 11:30pm)

  • Wednesday (10/2): Lecture
    • Review Python II: Iterable - Hashable vs. Mutable Problems 10-15
    • ASCII values
    • Discuss Academic Integrity Contract
      (turn in signed/dated copy on Friday, not today)

  • Thursday (10/3): Lab
    • Start Program #1: Iteration and Major Data Types
      (due on Tuesday, 10/15, at 11:30pm)
    • Program #0: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Friday (10/4): Lecture
    • Turn in signed/dated Academic Integrity Contract, at the start of class
    • Review Python III: Comprehensions - Trivial Things Problems 16a-17
    • Parameters: Including * and ** (examples)
    • Quiz #1: Download Quiz
      Eclipse Helper project for Quiz
      (Checkmate submission due on Thursday, 10/10, at 11:30pm;
      paper submission due on Friday, 10/11, in Lecture at the Start of Class)

Week 2

  • Monday (10/7): Lecture: Read EBNF Chapter, not Regular Expression Notes
    • EBNF: A Notation to Describe Syntax
      Problems: 1, 2, 6, 7
    • Typographic conventions for EBNF documenting Python

  • Tuesday (10/8): Lab
    • Work on Program #1: Iteration and Major Data Types
      (due on Tuesday, 10/15, at 11:30pm)

  • Wednesday (10/9): Lecture
    • Regular Expressions: Patterns
      Problems: 2, 4, 5, 7
    • Online regular expression tester (for Python)
      (select Python after clicking regular expressions 101 icon)
    • retester.py (Regular Expression Tester)

  • Thursday (10/10): Lab
    • Work on Program #1: Iteration and Major Data Types
      (due on Tuesday, 10/15, at 11:30pm)
    • Quiz #1: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Friday (10/11): Lecture
    • Quiz #1: Paper submission due in Lecture, at the start of class
    • Regular Expressions: Methods
      remethods (Folder with programs illustrating RE methods)
      Problems: 8, 9
    • Quiz #2: Download Quiz
      Eclipse Helper project for Quiz
      (due on Saturday, 10/19, at 11:30pm); extended because of In-Lab exam

Week 3

  • Monday (10/14): Lecture
    • Class Review
      Problems: 2, 3, 5
    • Demonstration: Leading Underscores for Attribute Names

  • Tuesday (10/15): Lab
    • Start Program #2: Classes, Overloaded Operators, Iterators
      (due on Tuesday, 10/29, at 11:30pm)
    • Program #1: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Wednesday (10/16): Lecture
    • Class Operator Overloading I
      Problems: 1, 2

  • Thursday (10/17): Lab
    • In-Lab Programming Exam I: Iteration and Major Data Types
    • Note: Quiz #2 is due at 11:30pm on Saturday 10/19

  • Friday (10/18): Lecture
    • Class Operator Overloading II
      Problems: 2, 4
    • Quiz #3: Download Quiz
      Eclipse Helper project for Quiz
      (due on Thursday, 10/24, at 11:30pm)

  • Saturday (10/19): Weekend (but Quiz #2 due; because not due Thursday)
    • Quiz #2: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

Week 4

  • Monday (10/21): Lecture
    • Iterator Protocol and Examples of Use
      Problems: 1,3, 4, 7
    • Picturing Countdown Iterator Object

  • Tuesday (10/22): Lab
    • Practice setting-up for In-Lab Programing Exam (given Thursday).
    • Work on Program #2: Classes, Overloaded Operators, Iterators
      (due on Tuesday, 10/29, at 11:30pm)

  • Wednesday (10/23): Lecture
    • Iterators in Classes with iter and next
      Problems: 1, 2, 4, 5
    • Picturing prange Object and its nested prange_iter class/a>
    • Aliasing/Copying in PH_iter

  • Thursday (10/24): Lab
    • Work on Program #2: Classes, Overloaded Operators, Iterators
      (due on Tuesday, 10/29, at 11:30pm)
    • Quiz #3: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Friday (10/25): Lecture
    • Generators (and yield): Functions that Act Like Iterators
      Problems: 2, 4, 5
    • Quiz #4: Download Quiz
      Eclipse Helper project for Quiz
      (due on Wednesday, 10/30, at 11:30pm)

Week 5

  • Monday (10/28): Lecture
    • Recursive Functions
      Problems: 1, 3, 6
      Recursion (implemented by the Cat in the Hat)
      Illustration for Recursion Joke

  • Tuesday (10/29): Lab
    • Start Program #3: namedtuple
      (due on Tuesday, 11/12, at 11:30pm)
    • Program #2: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Wednesday (10/30): Lecture
    • Functional Programming/Combinatorial Computing
      Problems 1, 3, 6, 7
    • Download stamps project (see stamps_basic/stamps_extended modules)
    • Download combinatorial project
    • Quiz #4: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Thursday (10/31): Lab
    • Midterm Written Exam
    • What is covered

  • Friday (11/1): Lecture
    • Decorators for Calling Functions
      Problem 1
    • Recursive Fibonnaci and Memoize
    • Memoize Decorating the fib Function
    • Optional: Decorators for Calling Tail Recursive Functions
    • Download decorator project
    • Download stamps project (see fast modules)
    • Optional Download decorators for tail recursion
    • Quiz #5: Download Quiz
      Eclipse Helper project for Quiz
      (due on Thursday, 11/7, at 11:30pm)

Week 6

  • Monday (11/4): Lecture
    • Linked Lists
      Problems: 1, 2, 4, 5
    • Pictures
    • Practice
    • Download linked list project

  • Tuesday (11/5): Lab
    • Work on Program #3: namedtuple
      (due on Tuesday, 11/12, at 11:30pm)

  • Wednesday (11/6): Lecture
    • Trees I
      Problems: 1, 3, 4, 5
    • Trees as Seen by Computer Scientists
    • Download tree project

  • Thursday (11/7): Lab
    • Work on Program #3: namedtuple
      (due on Tuesday, 11/12, at 11:30pm)
    • Quiz #5: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Friday (11/8): Lecture
    • Inheritance I
    • Examples of Method calls in Counter/ModularCounter
      Problems: 1-3
    • Download counters project
    • No Quiz distributed this week

Week 7

  • Monday (11/11): Lecture
    • Holiday (No Lecture): Veterans' Day

  • Tuesday (11/12): Lab
    • Start Program #4: Annotation Checker
      (due on Tuesday, 11/26, at 11:30pm)
    • Program #3: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Wednesday (11/13): Lecture
    • Inheritance II
    • Illegal Classes (because of Inheritance Network)
      Problems: 1
    • Download inheritance project

  • Thursday (11/14): Lab
    • In-Lab Programming Exam II: Classes, Overloaded Operators, and Iterators

  • Friday (11/15): Lecture
    • Inheritance III
    • Quiz #6: Download Quiz
      Eclipse Helper project for Quiz
      (Checkmate submission due on Thursday, 11/21, at 11:30pm;
      paper submission due on Friday, 11/22 in Lecture at the Start of Class)

Week 8

  • Monday (11/18): Lecture
    • Analysis of Algorithms and Complexity Classes

  • Tuesday (11/19): Lab
    • Work on Program #4: Annotation Checker
      (due on Tuesday, 11/26, at 11:30pm)

  • Wednesday (11/20): Lecture
    • The Complexity of Python Operators/Functions

  • Thursday (11/21): Lab
    • Work on Program #4: Annotation Checker
      (due on Tuesday, 11/26, at 11:30pm)
    • Quiz #6: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Friday (11/22): Lecture
    • Quiz #6: Paper submission due in Lecture, at the start of class
    • Empirical Efficiency: (up to but not including Hashing for sets and dicts)
    • Download empirical project
    • Quiz #7: Handed out in class; Download Quiz
      No Eclipse Helper project for Quiz
      (Paper submission due on Wednesday, 11/27, in Lecture at the Start of Class)

Week 9

  • Monday (11/25): Lecture
    • UnitTest
    • Download unittests project
    • View unittest pictures

  • Tuesday (11/26): Lab
    • Practice setting-up for In-Lab Programing Exam (given Thursday).
    • Start Program #5: Inheritance and Animation
      (due on Sunday, 12/8, at 11:30pm)
    • Program #4: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Wednesday (11/27): Lecture
    • Quiz #7: Paper submission due in Lecture, at the start of class
    • Finish Empirical Efficiency and UnitTest
    • Quiz #8: Download Quiz
      Eclipse Helper project for Quiz
      (due on Thursday, 12/5, at 11:30pm)

  • Thursday (11/28): Lab
    • Holiday (No Classes): Thanksgiving

  • Friday (11/29): Lecture
    • Holiday (No Classes): Thanksgiving

Week 10

  • Monday (12/2): Lecture
    • Python Machine [Code] (download disassembly project)

  • Tuesday (12/3): Lab
    • In-Lab Programming Exam III: Generator functions, Recursive functions (including Linked Lists and Trees), Decorators, Inheritance

  • Wednesday (12/4): Lecture
    • Introduction to Java: Static Typing/Collection Classes
    • and/or
    • Infinities in Mathematics and Computation: An Unsolvable Problem

  • Thursday (12/5): Lab
    • Work on Program #5: Inheritance and Animation
      (due on Sunday, 12/8, at 11:30pm)
    • Quiz #8: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

  • Friday (12/6): Lecture
    • Class Wrapup and What is covered on the Final Exam

  • Sunday (12/8): Last Day Before Final Exam Week
    • Program #5: Checkmate submission due at 11:30pm

Final Exams Week

  • Wednesday (12/11): Final Exam
    • 10:30am - 12:30pm
    • In our classroom PSLH 100
    • Instructions and seating assignments will be emailed before the exam
    • Bring a photo ID with a legible name and picture (UCI, drivers license, passport, etc.)
    • I will send email when I have computed/entered final grades, which are due to UCI by Thursday, December 19th at 5pm.
